      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3d7e8cf4_43463f82",
      "file_path": "catalog-be/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/components/impl/ResourceImportManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 206,
      "message": "I think the reading of the metadata should happen as part of the reading of the csar in CsarInfo getNodeTypesUsed rather than splitting this functionality, you would have somthing like:\n            mainTemplateImports.entrySet().forEach(entry -> {\n                final Map<String, Object> types = getTypesFromTemplate(entry.getValue(), TypeUtils.ToscaTagNamesEnum.NODE_TYPES, nodeTypesUsed);\n                final NodeTypeMetadata metadata = getMetaDataFromTemplate();\n                getTypesFromTemplate(entry.getValue(), TypeUtils.ToscaTagNamesEnum.NODE_TYPES, nodeTypesUsed);\nand return a type containginng both the map and the metadata",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
      },
      "updated": "2022-08-08 14:15:01.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
